About Chongqing Precision Biotech
Chongqing Precision Biotech is a biopharmaceutical company that focuses on the development of cell therapy technology. The company's main offerings include the research and development of CAR-T/NK cell drugs, which are used in the treatment of malignant tumors. The company serves the healthcare and pharmaceutical industries. It was founded in 2016 and is based in Chongqing, China.

Multiple Myeloma Overview
Multiple myeloma (MM) is a clonal plasma cell proliferative disorder characterized by the abnormal increase of monoclonal immunoglobulins. Unchecked, the excess production of these plasma cells can ultimately lead to specific end-organ damage. Most commonly, this is seen when at least one of the following clinical manifestations are present: hypercalcemia, renal dysfunction, anemia, or bone pain accompanied by lytic lesions. Japanese Company Eyes on Chongqing's Electronic Information Industry
Chongqing - Chongqing MasTek Electronics Co., Ltd., a joint venture between Japanese company Hoya Corporation and BOE Technology Group, recently began constructing its photomask project. With a total investment of 2.2 billion yuan (about USD 318.6 million), this initiative serves as the first large-scale project for photomask production equipment in the inland of China.
The launching ceremony of the photomask project in Liangjiang New Area. (Photo/Zhang Weizhen)
A photomask, a crucial tool for producing components such as electronic devices (semiconductors), displays, PCBs, and MEMS, serves as a master copy for patterning. The project is situated in Chongqing's Liangjiang New Area.
According to Takada Mari, Japanese Consul-General in Chongqing, the project stands as the most representative large-scale investment by Japanese companies in recent years. She believes the project will significantly contribute to the prosperity of Chongqing's electronic information industry.
Hoya Corporation, a world-leading photomask manufacturer, excels in the fields of optical imaging, electronic equipment and components, and medical devices. Meanwhile, BOE Technology Group ranks first in smartphones, tablets, laptops, and display device shipments. The collaboration between these two industry giants is expected to drive the industrial upgrade of display panels in Liangjiang New Area and complete the industrial chains in Chongqing and beyond.
Li Jie, Vice Director of Liangjiang New Area, said that the area serves as the primary hub for developing Chongqing's electronic information industry. It is accelerating the promotion of industrial quality and efficiency, focusing on new-type displays, integrated circuits, and intelligent terminals.
"Chongqing is a vital base for the BOE display industry. Since collaborating with Hoya in 2011, both companies have made rapid progress in their respective fields," said Cheng Gang, Vice President of BOE Technology Group. "The establishment of Chongqing MasTek Electronics Co., Ltd. plays a significant role in promoting the stability of display industry chains in China and beyond," he added.
It is worth noting that photomasks are essential components in the process of producing display panels, with their precision and quality directly affecting the yield rate. The project aims to begin mass production in the fourth quarter of 2024, boasting an annual capacity of approximately 2,250 photomask products valued at 700 million yuan.
The electronic information industry is the pillar of Liangjiang New Area. In 2022, the industry achieved an output value of 218.4 billion yuan, accounting for 30% of Chongqing's total. Moving forward, Liangjiang plans to drive Sichuan and Chongqing to establish a world-leading electronic information industrial cluster jointly.
